Peter SJOLIE, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7266. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 21, 1933. Allan A. Bynon, of Portland, Or., for appellant. Carl C. Donaugh, U. S. Atty., of Portland, Okl.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, consented to by counsel for appellant, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
